Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.12,0:02:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In October 1944, a landing fleet and convoy led by General MacArthur was gathered in the Leyte Gulf.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.02,0:02:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Second Fleet, led by Vice Admiral Takeo Kurita, set sail from Borneo via Brunei Bay with 39 Japanese ships,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.51,0:02:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,including the battleships Yamato, Musashino, Nagato, and the heavy cruiser Atago,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.16,0:02:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to destroy the American fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.75,0:03:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This operation, called Sho-ichigo, is a desperate operation for the Japanese Navy, which has been cornered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.00,0:03:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, the MTF of Vice Admiral Ozawa, whose flagship is the aircraft carrier Zuikaku,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.71,0:03:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced to the north of Luzon Island in the Philippines,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.21,0:03:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the MTF of the American side was transferred from the south,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.92,0:03:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,heading towards Leyte Gulf through the Surigao Strait.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.30,0:03:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The main force of the Kurita fleet runs through the San Bernardino Strait
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.52,0:03:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and plunges into Leyte Gulf off the coast of Samar Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, the Nishimura fleet was supposed to support the second fleet of Vice Admiral Shima.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.04,0:03:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Leyte Gulf (Part Two) (Episode 22)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:04:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this voyage was would meet with misfortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.24,0:04:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,First, on October 23rd, the flagship Atago and the heavy cruiser Maya
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.36,0:04:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,were attacked by a submarine and sank at Palawan Suido.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.16,0:04:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Takao was also wrecked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.26,0:05:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese cruiser is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.25,0:05:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack, only attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.40,0:05:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, on the 24th, the battleship Musashi was sunk by an air raid of 260 American attack aircraft in the Sibuyan Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.74,0:05:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The heavy cruiser Myoko was also attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.57,0:05:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.83,0:05:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.38,0:06:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop the main cannon from shooting!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.54,0:06:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, despite such a blow, the morale of the remaining 23 Japanese crews did not decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.18,0:06:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That is because it may be possible to bring about a decisive fleet battle
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.57,0:06:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,with the American Grand Fleet led by General Halsey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.30,0:06:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It was dawn of the following day, the 25th, that they skillfully escaped from the San Bernardino Strait,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.86,0:06:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which is said to be a difficult place, and went to the coast of Samar Island overlooking Luzon Bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.77,0:07:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Battle of Leyte Gulf, which was said to be a spectacular battle by the Japanese fleet, begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.10,0:07:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a quiet 50 km to Leyte.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.91,0:07:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's totally empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.63,0:07:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It may have been effective to show that we turned back at Sibuyan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.41,0:07:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the Ozawa fleet doing by the way? I haven't heard from them at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.66,0:07:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I will go to the operation room for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.42,0:07:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief. It is a signal from Kumano.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.73,0:07:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.49,0:07:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Found an enemy ship at 110 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.06,0:07:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.34,0:07:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Found enemy fleet, 125 degrees, distance 37,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. There can't be an enemy fleet so close, Isn't it a mistake? Look closely
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.50,0:07:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is. Ah
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.32,0:07:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an enemy aircraft carrier. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.95,0:07:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was good then that we come this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief. We can take them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.87,0:08:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is a convoy, attack the convoy, if it is a fleet, attack the fleet. Just do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.04,0:08:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief. Finally we can fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.26,0:08:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot. Why are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.85,0:08:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a reasonable response.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.79,0:08:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They have been training hard for a fleet battle with the enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.49,0:08:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but they could not bring about a decisive battle between fleets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.15,0:08:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, for those who were ordered to attack the convoy, it was nice to be able to fight with the battleship Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.42,0:08:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the realization of the Japanese Navy's dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.78,0:08:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Full power, immediate standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.42,0:08:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Line 130. Fire direction 110 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.28,0:08:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Line 130. Fire direction 110 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.80,0:09:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this discovery was not only made by the Japanese side but also on the American side.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.77,0:09:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We are a shooting gallery for the Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.27,0:09:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, launch all aircraft and evacuate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.76,0:09:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Raise a smoke screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.58,0:09:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let me call for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.07,0:09:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the closest fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The 77th, fourth, and second units.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.20,0:09:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. {Probably some missing lines here}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.26,0:09:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.63,0:09:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.24,0:09:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.13,0:09:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.26,0:09:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I am firing. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.27,0:09:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I am firing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.23,0:09:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet, Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.02,0:09:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the destroyer closed to range yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.62,0:09:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In Chief Kurita’s head, a tactic was drawn up in which a battleship and a cruiser would first
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.08,0:10:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,hit the deck of the enemy aircraft carrier, and then a destroyer would finish it with a torpedo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.84,0:10:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He was waiting for the destroyer to be in the perfect position.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm shooting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.24,0:10:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to escape. Please let me shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.72,0:10:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.74,0:10:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, start bombardment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.56,0:10:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.42,0:10:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,1 minute and 7 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.07,0:10:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.37,0:10:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's largest cannon on the battleship Yamato was fired in search of its first prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes one minute and seven seconds for a one and a half ton shell to reach the target.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.38,0:11:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Shell landing. First shell hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.34,0:11:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The giant guns fired all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.50,0:11:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, its the same as facing a tank in a shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.98,0:11:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.20,0:11:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, don't panic. I won't abandon you. Don't get excited. Don't be fooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.00,0:11:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.22,0:11:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about. They are adjusting their fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.37,0:11:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a squall. This is the same as putting up a smoke screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.58,0:11:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can't see the target, they can't hit us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.76,0:11:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It will stop soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.30,0:11:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Kurita could still attack the US fleet that was within range.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.72,0:11:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the squall became a god of help for the US Navy and prolonged the naval battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.78,0:11:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,During this time, the American side changed direction, widened their distance from the Kurita fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.94,0:12:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and was able to bring their destroyers forward enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.74,0:12:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Its finally our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.40,0:12:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Look for the huge one first.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.66,0:12:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ok. But the enemy's cannon Is ridiculously big.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.75,0:12:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too big. Even if it hits, it just penetrates and does not cause an explosion, it is rather easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.44,0:12:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it time to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.26,0:12:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Heavy cruiser ahead. Distance 18,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.84,0:12:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, it's an assault!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.44,0:12:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy cruiser is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.30,0:12:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So America does have some brave guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.04,0:12:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.07,0:12:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way, the battle off Samar has become turbulent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.17,0:12:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.60,0:13:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Now turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.24,0:13:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now look for the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.65,0:13:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.11,0:13:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE {or just leave untranslated, seems pretty obvious}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.49,0:13:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the next Japanese ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.08,0:13:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is good. It's a textbook torpedo attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.59,0:13:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.85,0:13:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Torpedo spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.93,0:13:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Full port!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.43,0:13:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Full port!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.56,0:14:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Torpedo spotted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.59,0:14:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a pincer attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.76,0:14:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Proceed as we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.92,0:14:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They seem to be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.69,0:14:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't steer to the right or left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.10,0:14:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no choice but to go straight until the torpedoes run dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.77,0:14:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finally time to leave the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.27,0:14:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamato was chased off by a torpedo and left the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.18,0:14:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The aircraft carrier Gambier Bay was sunk along with the destroyer Samuel Roberts and Johnston.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.70,0:15:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Fanshaw Bay and Kalinin Bay and the few remaining ships were shot at but escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Major General Sprague, who had been seeking help from the beginning, went higher up the command chain
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.99,0:15:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and asked his Lieutenant General Kinkaid, who defended the Philippines, for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.22,0:15:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But Kinkaid was far from the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.12,0:15:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,While relieved to annihilate the Nishimura fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.57,0:15:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,an escort carrier in the bay was suddenly attacked by a Japanese fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.90,0:15:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They are the Kamikaze corps of the Asahi and Kikusui corps that launched from Davao base that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.17,0:15:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The attack of the Kamikaze corps paralyzed Vice Admiral Kinkaid preventing him from going to Sprague's aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.96,0:16:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked Admiral Halsey to help the Sprague fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.78,0:16:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,General Halsey was far from the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.26,0:16:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When Halsey, who said the carrier fleet was their main objective, was informed of the discovery of the Ozawa fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.75,0:16:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he ignored the request for help from Vice Admiral Kinkaid and went north in search of the Ozawa MTF.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.42,0:17:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the Ozawa fleet, acting as a decoy, was brilliantly successful in distracting Halsey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.43,0:18:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,One light aircraft carrier on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.10,0:18:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, Halsey. I received another radio message.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.06,0:18:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinkaid's whining?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.57,0:18:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not the case. This is a message from General Nimitz in Guam.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.15,0:18:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why from Nimitz? Please read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.86,0:18:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,WHERE IS RPT WHERE IS TASK FORCE THIRTY FOUR RR
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fighting here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.42,0:18:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,THE WORLD WONDERS
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.08,0:18:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What? The world wonders?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.58,0:18:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that saying? Does he think I'm doing a hula dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.45,0:18:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.34,0:18:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants you to help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.59,0:18:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Nimitz does not speak out from the sidelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.61,0:18:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want to do? {Not sure, timing is all over the place in HA's translation}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I would like to go help him a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.44,0:18:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What a shame. I was looking forward to seeing what kind of hand Ozawa would play this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.10,0:19:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, leaving the rest to General Mitscher, he went south with the fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.51,0:19:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief. It's almost as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.14,0:19:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ugaki, I finally did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.52,0:19:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Finally Yamato's cannon was useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.42,0:19:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.62,0:19:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the result of the battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.25,0:19:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunk three or four ships, including the USS Enterprise, two cruisers, and one or two other aircraft carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.74,0:19:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.66,0:19:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, we must rush to Leyte Gulf before the enemy rescue team comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.62,0:19:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm actually thinking about that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.63,0:19:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.71,0:20:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this is fine. I was allowed to do a decisive fleet battle that I had been waiting for. And I won.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.67,0:20:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly this will change the result of the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.69,0:20:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you rush into Leyte as is, their rescue fleet will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.68,0:20:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,With that enemy as the last threat, our fleet may be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.68,0:20:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,As you say, we may be wiped out, but they have ordered us to enter Leyte Gulf.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.69,0:20:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.29,0:20:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it okay to sink the entire Japanese fleet here or preserve what we can and protect Japan for as long as possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the opposite. Isn't it just one more another push?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.70,0:20:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no information to go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.70,0:20:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on with Ozawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.93,0:20:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though the Nishimura fleet was wiped out, there are no detailed reports on the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.35,0:20:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are the enemies?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.34,0:20:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What are our allies doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.44,0:20:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly no information was gathered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.72,0:20:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No. What's happening with the Ozawa fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.36,0:20:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this is a fake message, it is from the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.23,0:21:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Halsey's plan text radio message: "I will go to the rescue in two hours."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.57,0:21:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they go to the rescue in two hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.65,0:21:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It is a tactic that they often use. We also do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.42,0:21:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We are in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.65,0:21:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, they did not know that the Ozawa fleet lured Halsey and had played the role of decoy so well,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.78,0:21:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,nor did they know that the Kamikaze corp's attack was successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.67,0:21:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It is better to rush in as we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.14,0:21:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why this strategy is meaningful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.68,0:21:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.83,0:21:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's time for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.54,0:21:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have any more information.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.51,0:21:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.02,0:21:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? There is nothing after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.69,0:21:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Let's come about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.43,0:21:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.03,0:21:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Full starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.03,0:21:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain. What are you doing? The enemy is over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.37,0:22:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, before entering Leyte Gulf, the Kurita fleet suddenly turned around and pulled out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.97,0:22:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese fleet is moving north and pulling out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.97,0:22:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.36,0:22:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It was rather the Combined Fleet's General Headquarters in Hiyoshidai that was surprised at their reversal
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.66,0:22:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,ahead of their entry into Leyte Gulf.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.26,0:22:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately after receiving the news of the course change by the Kurita fleet, an encouraging radio message was sent.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.49,0:22:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering the damage of each fleet and their sailors, I think the enemy is in a more difficult situation than us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.56,0:22:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, you should proceed to the operation point regardless of sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.88,0:22:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Radio message from the Commander-in-Chief of the Allied Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.76,0:23:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there was no fleet that responded to this encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.20,0:23:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It is said that Chief Kurita’s decision to reverse in front of the enemy is a mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.28,0:23:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that will remain forever in the history of naval warfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.34,0:23:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but at that time, Lieutenant General Kurita’s mind was preoccupied with the idea of decisive fleet battle
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.82,0:23:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the possible results of that battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.98,0:23:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Lack of fuel, lack of information on enemies and allies, etc. {Seems like this etc. is just HA being lazy}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.30,0:23:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This teaches us that important decisions always require information,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.75,0:23:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and how the right information is gathered is a key factor in making a decision,
